                <div class="detail-title">FROM CHAT TO ACTION</div>
                <div class="detail-body">
                    We are witnessing a phase shift. Generative AI allowed machines to <em>speak</em>. Agentic AI allows machines to <em>do</em>. <br><br>
                    Agents can now plan complex workflows, use software tools, and execute transactions autonomously. But this power creates a new vector of corporate risk.
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 2. THE RISK LANDSCAPE -->
        <section id="sec-2" class="right-align">
            <div class="super-text" style="-webkit-text-stroke-color: rgba(255, 50, 50, 0.5);">THE ACTION <br><span class="highlight" style="color: var(--alert)">GAP</span></div>
            <div class="detail-box" style="border-color: var(--alert);">
                <div class="detail-title">WHEN HALLUCINATIONS CLICK BUTTONS</div>
                <div class="detail-body">
                    In GenAI, a mistake means a wrong sentence. In Agentic AI, a mistake could mean a wrong payment, a deleted database, or a security breach.<br><br>
                    Traditional cybersecurity protects systems from outsiders. We now need architectures that protect systems from <em>insider</em> AI agents.
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 3. ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW -->
        <section id="sec-3" class="center-align">
            <div class="super-text">THE SAFETY <br><span class="highlight">STACK</span></div>
            <div class="detail-box" style="border: 1px solid #fff; text-align: center;">
                <div class="detail-title">DEFENSE IN DEPTH</div>
                <div class="detail-body">
                    McKinsey proposes a multi-layered safety architecture. It's not just about "better prompting." It requires hard-coded engineering guardrails that sit <em>outside</em> the neural network.
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 4. INPUT FILTERS -->
        <section id="sec-4">
            <div class="super-text">LAYER 01 <br><span class="highlight" style="color: var(--laser-blue)">FILTRATION</span></div>
            <div class="detail-box" style="border-color: var(--laser-blue);">
                <div class="detail-title">INPUT & OUTPUT GUARDRAILS</div>
                <div class="detail-body">
                    <strong>Input:</strong> Scan prompts for injection attacks (e.g., "Ignore previous instructions").<br>
                    <strong>Output:</strong> Verify agent decisions against policy before execution. If an agent tries to transfer >$10k, a hard-coded circuit breaker must trip.
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 5. DETERMINISTIC EXECUTION -->
        <section id="sec-5" class="right-align">
            <div class="super-text">LAYER 02 <br><span class="highlight" style="color: var(--success)">VERIFICATION</span></div>
            <div class="detail-box" style="border-color: var(--success);">
                <div class="detail-title">CODE > PROBABILITIES</div>
                <div class="detail-body">
                    LLMs are probabilistic (they guess). Business logic must be deterministic (it knows).<br><br>
                    <strong>The Solution:</strong> Agents should write code to solve math or logic problems, then execute that code in a sandbox. Don't ask the LLM to calculate; ask it to write a Python script that calculates.
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 6. HUMAN OVERSIGHT -->
        <section id="sec-6">
            <div class="super-text">LAYER 03 <br><span class="highlight" style="color: var(--lux-gold)">OVERSIGHT</span></div>
            <div class="detail-box">
                <div class="detail-title">HUMAN-ON-THE-LOOP</div>
                <div class="detail-body">
                    <strong>In-the-Loop:</strong> Human approves every step (Too slow, unscalable).<br>
                    <strong>On-the-Loop:</strong> Human sets goals and monitors dashboards. The system alerts the human only when confidence scores drop below a threshold.
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 7. SHIFT LEFT -->
        <section id="sec-7" class="center-align">
            <div class="super-text">SHIFT <br><span class="highlight">LEFT</span></div>
            <div class="detail-box">
                <div class="detail-title">TESTING & RED TEAMING</div>
                <div class="detail-body">
                    Safety begins before deployment. "Red Teaming" involves hiring experts to try and break your agent—forcing it to do illegal or harmful things—to patch vulnerabilities before they go live.
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 8. GOVERNANCE -->
        <section id="sec-8" class="right-align">
